We had to say goodbye to our sweet Elliot a couple days ago, 14 epic years with this guy. One of the hardest things @heysebree and I had to do in our 17 years of marriage. He was perfect 💔 
Haley summed it up best in her post so I’ll share her words below. I don’t have the steam yet to write anything close to what she said💔
-Haley 
“14 years ago while driving home from church Kylle made the mistake of stopping ‘just to look’ at the one remaining puppy in the back of the pick-up truck with the writing on the windows, “labradoodles for sale”. We sat in the parking lot for close to 2 hours with me holding the puppy and him saying, “Haley, I’ve never seen you this irrational. We can’t get a puppy right now.” We had just moved back to Texas from Hawaii, hadn’t started our jobs yet and our apartment wasn’t ready to move in for another 2 weeks. Kylle finally told me to “call the voice of reason” (my mom), thinking she would talk me out of it. She showed up within 5 minutes and we were soon on our way with a tiny (16lbs), 7 1/2 wk old puppy who we named, Elliot. 

Elliot moved with us from TX to CA to Canada, back to CA to TX again and finally back to CA. He was there as we’ve started a business, moved shops, struggled through infertility, welcomed home a baby girl and saw me through most of this pregnancy. 
He was always the best pup, putting himself in timeout in the bathtub as a young guy, always being ready for a game of fetch and never skipping on a trail walk. He seamlessly adapted when Maizy came home and welcomed her into his pack. Always the best companion for our family. 

He selflessly gave and always loved. 
 
We always imagined when he ran in his  dreams he was running through Cliff Gilker, his favorite park on the Sunshine Coast of BC. Yesterday was really hard, we had to say goodbye as he ran over the rainbow bridge. May he be running free and without pain or a cough. We will always have a sweet Elliot sized hole missing. 
Run in paradise, my sweet friend. 💔”
